</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1142,1599]" pageId="9" pageNumber="304">
Before this study, the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1926" box="[477,549,1142,1167]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Buyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[477,549,1142,1167]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="304">Buyda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was represented in the Neotropics by two species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gerstaecker)" authorityName="Gerstaecker" baseAuthorityName="Gerstaecker" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[1139,1435,1142,1167]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Buyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phthisica">
<emphasis box="[1139,1275,1142,1167]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="304">B. phthisica</emphasis>
(Gerstaecker)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Navas. The" authorityName="Navas. The" authorityYear="1926" box="[200,454,1178,1203]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Buyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicata">
<emphasis box="[200,316,1180,1203]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="304">B. apicata</emphasis>
Navás. The
</taxonomicName>
second species is herein synonymized with the former, as proposed in the revisionary work by Hoffman (1992), being 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gerstaecker" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[535,673,1214,1239]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Buyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phthisica">
<emphasis box="[535,673,1214,1239]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="304">B. phthisica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the only valid species of this genus until now. The geographical distribution of this species ranges from 
<collectingCountry box="[596,705,1250,1275]" name="Honduras" pageId="9" pageNumber="304">Honduras</collectingCountry>
to southern 
<collectingCountry box="[845,956,1250,1275]" name="Argentina" pageId="9" pageNumber="304">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[971,1142,1250,1275]" pageId="9" pageNumber="304" refId="ref17407" refString="Hoffman, K. M. (2002) Family Mantispidae. In Penny, N. D. (ed.), A guide to the lacewings (Neuroptera) of Costa Rica. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 53 (12), 251 - 275." type="journal article">Hoffman 2002</bibRefCitation>
). Here, we describe a new species for this genus, which was previously described from 
<collectingRegion box="[842,931,1287,1310]" country="Panama" name="Panama" pageId="9" pageNumber="304">
<collectingCountry box="[842,931,1287,1310]" name="Panama" pageId="9" pageNumber="304">Panama</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
in Hoffman’s Ph.D. dissertation of 1992 but was not formally published by the author. This new species presents a body color pattern, genital morphology and arrangement of the abdominal pregenital apparatus remarkably different from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gerstaecker" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[1061,1199,1358,1383]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Buyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phthisica">
<emphasis box="[1061,1199,1358,1383]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="304">B. phthisica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation pageId="9" pageNumber="304" refId="ref16776" refString="Ardila-Camacho, A. &amp; Garcia, A. (2015) Mantidflies of Colombia (Neuroptera, Mantispidae). Zootaxa, 3937 (3), 401 - 455. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3937.3.1" type="journal article">Ardila-Camacho &amp; García (2015)</bibRefCitation>
reported this species as inquirenda from the departments of 
<collectingRegion box="[1030,1142,1394,1419]" country="Colombia" name="Antioquia" pageId="9" pageNumber="304">Antioquia</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1205,1269,1395,1419]" country="Venezuela" name="Sucre" pageId="9" pageNumber="304">Sucre</collectingRegion>
based on two female specimens. According to 
<bibRefCitation box="[537,932,1430,1455]" pageId="9" pageNumber="304" refId="ref16776" refString="Ardila-Camacho, A. &amp; Garcia, A. (2015) Mantidflies of Colombia (Neuroptera, Mantispidae). Zootaxa, 3937 (3), 401 - 455. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3937.3.1" type="journal article">Ardila-Camacho &amp; García (2015)</bibRefCitation>
, the examination of male specimens could clarify the identity of these specimens, either as specimens pertaining to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gerstaecker" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[966,1101,1466,1491]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Buyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phthisica">
<emphasis box="[966,1101,1466,1491]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="304">B. phthisica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or as the species described as new in the Hoffman´s dissertation, given the morphological similitude of female specimens. In the present study, we describe this species with consent of K.M. Hoffman (pers. comm.). The species description is based on the work by Hoffman (1992) and our own examination of a series of specimens housed in 
<collectionCode box="[1121,1197,1575,1599]" pageId="9" pageNumber="304">CEUA</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode box="[1252,1375,1575,1599]" pageId="9" pageNumber="304">ANDES-E</collectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
